  "definitions": [
    {
      "source": "SMI",
      "text": "(Acts 18:3; 19:25; Revelation 18:22) A trade was taught to ail the Jewish boys as a necessary part of their education. Even the greatest rabbis maintained themselves by trades (Delitzsch). Says Rabbi Jehuda, “He who does not teach his son a trade is much the same as if he taught him to be a thief”. In the present article brief notice only can be given of such handicraft trades as are mentioned in Scripture.",
